    "steps": [
      "In a spice grinder, grind bay leaves, cumin, coriander, oregano, and peppercorns until very finely ground. Set aside.",
      "Heat lard or oil in a large heavy pot over medium-high heat. Brown ribs in batches, turning once, until browned on at least 2 sides, 5–7 minutes per batch. Transfer to a large bowl.",
      "To the same pot, add onion and salt, cooking until browned and tender, about 8–10 minutes. Stir occasionally, scraping up browned bits from the bottom of the pan.",
      "Add the spice blend and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add poblanos, tomatillos, jalapeños, and garlic, stirring occasionally, until tender and just starting to brown, about 8–10 minutes.",
      "Return the ribs to the pot and add 2 cups of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the ribs are tender and falling off the bone, 2–2 ½ hours.",
      "Let sit covered for 15 minutes. Stir in scallions and cilantro before serving. Serve with warm tortillas and frijoles de olla.",
      "A dish made with love—enjoy every spoonful!"
